The paper deals with communication lower bounds for distributed statistical estimation problems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, the use of message passing and the focus on communication complexity suggest that the paper is most likely to be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The mention of sparse linear regression and the use of sparsity constraints also suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant sub-category. The mention of a distributed data processing inequality suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the mention of multi-round iterative communication model suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) could be a relevant sub-category as well.
